John's beat Wagner 79-68 Saturday in Norm Roberts' debut as coach
of the Red Storm.
article.headline: Hill's 20 points pace St. John's
article.linkText: St. John's makes Roberts a winner in debut
article.story:
NEW YORK (AP) -- Darryll Hill scored a game-high 20 points and St. John's beat Wagner 79-68 Saturday in Norm Roberts' debut as coach of the Red Storm.

Roberts, an assistant at Kansas last season, replaced the fired Mike Jarvis in April and took over a team coming off a 6-21 season.

Freshman Dexter Gray scored 17 points and Lamont Hamilton added 13 for the Red Storm, who held a 43-27 lead at the break.

Joey Mundweiler scored 16 points for the Seahawks, who haven't beaten St. John's since 1956.

Hamilton scored the first and last points of a 14-0 run that gave the Red Storm a 21-7 lead midway through the first half. Wagner closed within four, before Gray scored six points in a 15-4 outburst that helped St. John's regain control.

Wagner closed within 54-50 with 12 minutes remaining, but St. John's extended its lead to double figures with a 7-1 run.
